# Sharpee Multiuser Server — Docker build context filter.
#
# The build context is the repo root (the Dockerfile reaches into
# ../../packages/core). This file keeps the context minimal: only the two
# trees that `tools/server/Dockerfile` COPYs are shipped to the daemon.
#
# Pattern: ignore everything, then re-include packages/core and tools/server,
# then prune dev/build artifacts inside those trees.

# Ignore everything by default.
**

# Re-include the two trees the Dockerfile copies.
!package.json
!pnpm-workspace.yaml
!pnpm-lock.yaml

!packages
!packages/**

!tools
!tools/server
!tools/server/**

# Prune dev/build artifacts inside the included trees.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/dist-cjs
**/dist-npm
**/coverage
**/.turbo
**/.next
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
**/.git
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Re-include packages' pre-built dist trees (required at runtime — `pnpm
# deploy --prod` materialises them into the runtime image, and Node ESM
# resolution after ADR-162 reaches into dist/ for @sharpee/world-model).
!packages/*/dist
!packages/*/dist/**
!packages/*/dist-esm
!packages/*/dist-esm/**
